  "prompt": "Are there any other straight men diagnosed with histrionic personality disorder?",
  "response": "Yes, histrionic personality disorder (HPD) can affect individuals of any gender or sexual orientation, including straight men. While the disorder is often associated with women, it is essential to understand that personality disorders do not discriminate based on gender or sexual orientation. The key characteristics of HPD include a pattern of excessive emotionality and attention-seeking behavior, which can manifest in anyone, regardless of these factors.\n\nDiagnoses are based on individual symptoms and behaviors, not gender or sexual orientation. If you are looking for specific cases or examples, these might be less documented due to the lower overall diagnosis rates in men, but they certainly exist. Mental health professionals can provide more personalized insights or treatment options addressing this condition.",
